      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IRK MCGLURK (1) has been racing well from wider or second row barriers, placing in two of three starts since he worked but proved too good at Forbes last month. Raced parked but stuck on for a 2.7m third at Bathurst last week. Should get his chance from the ace draw. LOLLIPOP (10) turned in another strong performance last start when she battled on bravely to just miss out by a nose at Bathurst. No favours expected from this draw but she has placed in three of four starts since a Canberra win and she came from a similar barrier to this when third last month at Forbes. SHEZ A PUNTER (9) resumes after three-and-a-half months but would measure right up if she reproduced a fine effort at Bathurst two back when beaten just a head into second. SHEZ A WARRIOR (7) led and kept going in a last-start win by 3.6 metres at Dubbo. Draws for a trail and could be dangerous again if she gets the gaps.",
